---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  locale="en"
  eyebrow="Privacy"
  title="Privacy policy"
  description="Scluba's privacy policy — what data we collect, why, legal basis, retention, recipients and your GDPR rights."
  altPathname="/legal/confidentialite/"
  updated="2026-05-06"
>
  <p class="legal-callout">
    <strong>GDPR commitment</strong>
    Scluba processes personal data in compliance with EU Regulation 2016/679 (GDPR) and the French
    Data Protection Act of 6 January 1978 as amended. This policy describes, transparently, what we
    collect, why, and the rights you have.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
  <p>
    The controller of personal data collected via <a href="https://scluba.com">scluba.com</a> and
    the Scluba application (hereinafter <strong>"Scluba"</strong>) is:
  </p>
  <p>
    Grégoire GUILLOT & Paul MICHEL<br />
    Address available on request at team@scluba.com<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:team@scluba.com">team@scluba.com</a><br />
    Representative: Grégoire GUILLOT & Paul MICHEL — co-founders
  </p>
  <p>
    Scluba does not exceed the thresholds requiring the appointment of a Data Protection Officer
    (DPO). For any request regarding your data, the single point of contact is:
    <a href="mailto:team@scluba.com">team@scluba.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data we collect</h2>

  <h3>2.1 Data collected from website visitors (prospect clubs)</h3>
  <p>
    When you request a demo through the contact form, we collect:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>your <strong>name</strong> and your <strong>work email</strong>;</li>
    <li>the <strong>name of your golf club</strong>;</li>
    <li>the <strong>communications</strong> you initiate with us (emails, calls).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.2 Data collected from players (end users)</h3>
  <p>
    When a player scans a partner club's QR code to use Scluba, we collect, depending on usage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>the <strong>scores</strong> entered (hole by hole, total, par);</li>
    <li><strong>GPS location</strong> during the round <em>(only if authorized by the browser or app — purpose: course tracking)</em>;</li>
    <li>the <strong>duration</strong> and <strong>distance</strong> traveled;</li>
    <li>if you create a player account (optional): <strong>email</strong>, <strong>first name</strong>, and round history;</li>
    <li><strong>technical data</strong> (device type, system, browser version) for stability purposes.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.3 Automatically collected data</h3>
  <p>
    Like any website, Scluba automatically logs certain technical information: anonymized IP
    address, pages visited, timestamp, approximate country. This data is used solely for security
    and aggregated statistics.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Purposes and legal bases</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Purpose</th><th>Legal basis (GDPR)</th><th>Retention</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Reply to a demo / club contact request</td>
        <td>Pre-contractual measures (art. 6.1.b)</td>
        <td>3 years after last contact</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Performance of the contract with the partner club</td>
        <td>Contract performance (art. 6.1.b)</td>
        <td>Contract duration + 5 years (commercial limitation period)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Score entry / GPS tracking for players</td>
        <td>Consent (art. 6.1.a) — scanning the QR code constitutes acceptance</td>
        <td>Session duration + 90 days, or until account deletion</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Player account creation and management</td>
        <td>Consent (art. 6.1.a)</td>
        <td>Until user-initiated deletion, or 3 years of inactivity</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Aggregated reporting to the club (scans, rounds, shares)</td>
        <td>Legitimate interest (art. 6.1.f) — anonymized data</td>
        <td>Club contract duration + 1 year</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Security, logging, fraud prevention</td>
        <td>Legitimate interest (art. 6.1.f)</td>
        <td>12 months</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Accounting and tax obligations</td>
        <td>Legal obligation (art. 6.1.c)</td>
        <td>10 years</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>4. Recipients</h2>
  <p>
    Your data is only accessible to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>authorized <strong>Scluba teams</strong> (support, technical, sales) within the scope of their duties;</li>
    <li>the <strong>partner golf club</strong> through which you use the service, only for the data needed for reporting (scans, rounds, shares — aggregated);</li>
    <li>our <strong>technical sub-processors</strong> listed below, acting on documented instructions and bound by contract in accordance with article 28 GDPR;</li>
    <li><strong>competent authorities</strong> in the event of judicial or administrative requisition.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>We never sell your data.</strong> We do not share it with any third party for commercial or
    advertising purposes.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Sub-processors and transfers outside the EU</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Provider</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Location</th><th>Safeguards</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Netlify, Inc.</td>
        <td>Site hosting and CDN</td>
        <td>United States</td>
        <td>EU Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC), Data Privacy Framework</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Supabase Inc.</td>
        <td>Database and authentication</td>
        <td>EU — region eu-central-1 (Frankfurt)</td>
        <td>EU hosting, Supabase DPA</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Resend / Resend (Resend Inc., USA) — transit only, no storage</td>
        <td>Sending transactional emails (demo, notifications)</td>
        <td>EU / United States</td>
        <td>EU Standard Contractual Clauses</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    When data is transferred outside the European Union, it is transferred to countries with an
    adequate level of protection (Commission decision) or covered by appropriate safeguards
    (Standard Contractual Clauses, Data Privacy Framework).
  </p>

  <h2>6. Security</h2>
  <p>
    Scluba implements appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your data: TLS
    encryption on all communications, secure hosting, role-based access control, logging of
    sensitive accesses, regular backups, security updates, and a strong password policy for our
    team.
  </p>
  <p>
    In the event of a data breach posing a risk to your rights and freedoms, Scluba will notify
    the CNIL within 72 hours and, where applicable, will inform you directly.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    In accordance with articles 15 to 22 of the GDPR, you have the following rights over your data:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Right of access</strong> — to know whether we process your data and obtain a copy;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> — to correct inaccurate or incomplete data;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> ("right to be forgotten") — to request deletion of your data;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to restriction</strong> — to restrict processing in certain situations;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> — to receive your data in a structured, readable format;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to object</strong> — to object to processing based on legitimate interest;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> at any time, without affecting the lawfulness of prior processing;</li>
    <li><strong>Right to set post-mortem directives</strong> on the fate of your data after your death.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise these rights, write to <a href="mailto:team@scluba.com">team@scluba.com</a>
    specifying your request. We will reply within one month, extendable by two months for complex
    requests. Proof of identity may be requested in the event of reasonable doubt about the
    identity of the requester.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you believe that the processing of your data does not comply with the regulations, you have
    the right to lodge a complaint with the French data protection authority (<strong>CNIL</strong>):
    <a href="https://www.cnil.fr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.cnil.fr</a> — 3 Place de
    Fontenoy, TSA 80715, 75334 Paris Cedex 07.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Automated decisions and profiling</h2>
  <p>
    Scluba does not carry out any automated decision-making producing legal effects on you, nor any
    profiling for advertising targeting purposes. Usage statistics generated for the partner club
    are aggregated and do not allow your individual identification.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Minors</h2>
  <p>
    Scluba is not intended for persons under 15 years of age (digital consent threshold in France).
    We do not knowingly collect data from minors without the authorization of those holding
    parental responsibility. If you believe a minor has provided us with data without such
    authorization, contact us: we will proceed with deletion.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    The use of cookies on the Site is detailed in our dedicated
    <a href="/en/legal/cookies/">Cookie policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Policy changes</h2>
  <p>
    Scluba may update this policy to reflect legal, technical or organizational changes. The
    applicable version is the one in force when you visit, dated at the top of the page. Any
    substantial change will be notified to you if we have a contact channel.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For any questions about your data: <a href="mailto:team@scluba.com">team@scluba.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
